Bold strokes and collaged imagery define Ellie Foreman-Peck’s (@elliefp) signature style. We couldn’t love it more. As a London based illustrator, her work includes larger-than-life caricatures and bold editorial prints that visualize charming stories. From paintings and animations to ceramics and posters, she’s inspired by classic painters and traditional techniques.

Recently we teamed up with her to visualize Hotel Indigo Galapagos through a vivid neighborhood-inspired illustration. Set on the enchanting San Cristóbal Island, an area known for its tranquil vibe, dreamy blue hues of the sea, and varied wildlife–our hotel lives in a modern-day paradise. Ellie’s vision for the illustration came to life, beautifully blending the color of the sea, flittering yellow warblers, and drawings and notes by Charles Darwin from his adventures on the island.

Lovingly restored and converted from a department store building dating back to 1792, @hotelindigoexeter has opened its doors.​

Pride Month, but make it Boston ❤️ Did you know that many of Boston's historically queer spaces weren’t preserved? As you venture through the city this June and beyond, take some time out to delve into the histories of iconic places, pivotal moments and formation of groundbreaking collectives like the 1970 Christopher Street Liberation Day Rally, Boston LGBT Film Festival, Boston Gay Men’s Chorus and the legendary Napoleon Club.

@BostonPrideforthePeople is back this year on June 10! Staying with us at @HotelIndigoBoston during your celebrations? Be sure to tag @HotelIndigo so we can spread the love 🌈

Spirits and self-expression soar in Madrid’s lively neighborhood of Chueca ✨As you walk the streets you’ll find the most charming balconies, and dozens of flags fluttering with pride. 

The bustling haven exudes energy and a spirit of bold inclusivity. If you're lucky enough to be there during Pride, you’ll have the chance to experience the dazzling #MadridPride parade. Get ready to embrace Chueca's exuberant embrace, where acceptance knows no absolutely no bounds. 🏳️‍🌈

The captivating city of Glasgow’s LGBTQIA+ history just can’t be overlooked. If you find yourself in the area this summer, check out the Lesbian Archive within Glasgow's Women's Library. Established in 1991, the library continues to collaborate with lesbian community members and collectives to ensure that archives thoughtfully capture the experiences of lesbian women. Journey through this curated collection to discover the vibrant narratives and contributions of the lesbian community throughout time.

Glasgow Pride is July 15! And if you happen to be staying at @IndigoGlasgow, be sure to tag us (we’d love to see you)! 🌈

Postcards from Dundee, Scotland. This historic city became popular in the 12th century as an important east coast trading post. Today, @hotelindigo_dundee resides in what once was a historical jute and linen mill. Look closely and you'll see nods to the heritage and neighborhood woven into the very fabric of the hotel (see what we did there?).

Last night in partnership with @People, we hosted country music star, @MegMoroney, at Hotel Indigo @CountrypolitanNashville where she performed an exclusive concert for some of her biggest fans, including @ihgonerewards members. Guess you can say we are feeling pretty LUCKY. 🍀

Hey there, neighbor. 👋

We're constantly inspired by our local communities (that's you!), so we wanted to do a little something to invite you into our spaces. Introducing our new ‘Borrowed by Hotel Indigo’ program where locals can borrow everyday necessities (think a cup of sugar, coffee, tea, olive oil, etc.) at select Hotel Indigos in the US and UK! For those just visiting looking for a taste of the neighborhood to take back home, we'll also have special locally-inspired items to take back home with you. 

P.S. Just like a real neighbor, you get to keep what you #BorrowedbyHotelIndigo.​

Don your walking shoes, Brussels City is calling. Belgium's capital is brimming with UNESCO architectural sites, botanical gardens, and incredible street art.

Once you work up an appetite, you'll find plenty of options with more than 138 restaurants per square mile. Stop by @serrabrussels to enjoy local, seasonal, natural and feel-good food. (Trust us, it'll hit the spot after all that Belgium chocolate.)

And when the day is finished, you can rest your tired legs @hotelindigobrusselscity.

Welcome to IHG’s Winter Chalet ❄️🧣☃️ @ihghotels @hotelindigodtla — 

This pop up winter chalet feels like a cozy & warm mountain retreat after a long day of being on the slopes. From signature beverages like graham cracker espresso martinis, to seasonal bites over classic board games, IHG’s Winter Chalet will leave you feeling like you’re at a luxury alpine escape. 

The Winter Chalet pop up installations will run until the end of February at different locations, from the one we visited in Downtown LA at @hotelindigodtla to locations in Atlanta, Chicago, San Diego, and more.
